t: Access control list (ACL) overview - Amazon Simple Storage Service
s: Amazon S3 access control lists (ACLs) enable you to manage access to buckets and objects. Each bucket and object has an ACL attached to it as a subresource. It defines which AWS accounts or groups are granted access and the type of access.

t: Using web ACLs in AWS WAF - AWS WAF, AWS Firewall Manager, and AWS Shield Advanced
s: A web ACL gives you fine-grained control over all of the HTTP(S) web requests that your protected resource responds to. You can protect Amazon CloudFront, Amazon API Gateway, Application Load Balancer, AWS AppSync, Amazon Cognito, AWS App Runner, AWS Amplify, and AWS Verified Access resources.

t: Configuring ACLs - Amazon Simple Storage Service
